Table 2
summarises biological data for patient 2. Chest radiograph showed upper right lobe consolidation (figure 2A
). Oxygen therapy at 3 L/min and piperacillin plus tazobactam were started on April 30. The initial nasopharyngeal sample was inconclusive. The patient remained stable but with a high fever (39–40°C) between May 9 and May 12. Linezolid was added to the antimicrobial regimen on May 11. Diagnosis of MERS-CoV infection was confirmed on the basis of results from induced sputum analysis on May 11. Personal protective equipment—an FFP2 mask, gloves, gown, and goggles—was used to prevent secondary transmission during sputum induction.
